line_1: Youth shall in crowds before you kneel,
line_2: But soon those eyes their strength shall feel;

line_1: To quell that servile band, who kneel
Thus brides again and bridegrooms blithe shall kneel,
line_2: By love or law compell'd their vows to seal,

line_1: I scarcely can forbear to kneel.
To Thee, with shame-torn heart, I trembling kneel;
line_2: Heal me with mercy; oh! my Saviour, heal!
That o'er thy senses soft shall steal

line_1: Dare at the Feet of her great Sovereign kneel;
line_2: Bless'd with such hopes, my Muse, with Prostrate Zeal,

line_1: As humble vot'ries at thine altars kneel.
line_2: Thy cruel and malignant influence feel;

line_1: As with raised hands the suppliant traitors kneel
line_2: And fear the vengeance they deserve to feel,

line_1: To thee, protectress of my lays, I kneel;
line_2: While parties rage, O Truth! with honest zeal
